title: t-62
body: Soviet cold war era tank. Intended as the successor of the T-55 it was of limited success due to advances in munition technologies. Merely supplemented T-55s in Soviet service although many were still produced and exported to numerous countries. Fought in many wars, most recently the Syrian Civil war. Currently still in service in a number of countries, many upgraded over the years.

title: scharnhorst
body: Battlecruiser, lead ship of her class. Designed after the Anglo-German Naval Agreement of 1935 as a response to the dunkerque class. Was with her sister in most missions during the early part of the war. Was sunk by HMS Duke of York in 1943 when she attempted to intercept a convoy bound for Russia.

title: gneisenau
body: Battlecruiser of the Scharnhorst class. Was with her sister in most missions during the early part of the war. Heavily damaged after the Channel Dash and was selected for conversion to accept 15in guns. Conversion never took place due to the deteriorating war situation. Scuttled in 1945.

title: soul_edge_(weapon)
body:
[b]Soul Edge[/b] is the central antagonist in the [[soulcalibur|Soul series]] of fighting games and namesake to [[soul edge|the first installment]], a legendary living weapon that seeks to reap souls for power. Originally forged by human hands, at first Soul Edge was just an ordinary sword, but after being bathed in blood and hatred countless times, the sword turned into a demonic weapon and gained a wicked soul called Inferno. Those who grasp its hilt are unable to escape its curse, as its spirit invades the mind like a parasite and drives its wielder insane. As its blade is soaked in blood, it grows in power, yet it manages to shine a polished red. Even when broken into small shards, its influence is still felt. Soul Edge is distinguished by the animate eye and is known to take the form of whatever is most convenient for its wielder.

Soul Edge's most famous owners include the dread pirate [[Cervantes de Leon]], the Azure Knight [[Nightmare (Soulcalibur)|Nightmare]], and [[Pyrrha Alexandra]].

Soul Edge is diametrically opposed by its sibling weapon, [[Soul Calibur (weapon)|Soul Calibur]].

title: richelieu_(battleship)
body:
Lead ship of her class, built in response to Italian battleship constructions. Overall design roughly similar to that of Dunkerque class (quadruple main armament turret, main armament all concentrated forward). The only class of French battleship armed with 15in guns...

To quote from Conway

"Richelieu was 95 per cent complete when France surrendered and she proceeded to Dakar, where she was damaged during the British attack. In 1942 she joined the Allies and was sent to the USA for a major refit, emerging in October 1943 with radar added, aircraft and catapults removed, ...

... Richelieu was employed with the British Eastern Fleet in 1944-45 and later off French Indo-China. She paid off in 1959 and was hulked at Brest as an accommodation ship."

title: internet_positif
body:
Internet Positif is an [[Indonesian]] internet-filtering service that the Ministry of Communication and Information uses to block websites about topics such as gambling, pornography, phishing, racism and incitement of religious antagonism, or proxies. But because popular websites such as Reddit also got blocked, there has been much protest against the service and its initiator, the then-Minister of Communication and Information "Tifatul Sembiring":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tifatul_Sembiring].

As of August 2015, Internet Positif has officially blocked Danbooru from Indonesian access (it can be circumvented through proxies, though).

Most notable for providing inspiration for the character [[Ipo-chan]].

title: sakura_mami
body:
The main character of [[Esper Mami]], a series by the same artistic team behind [[Doraemon]].

Mami is a French-Japanese girl with supernatural powers -- the insinuation is that she is a descendant of French witches.  She uses her supernatural powers alongside her tanuki-like pet dog and [[Takahata Kazuo]], her best friend (and secret-keeper).

Mami's father is a painter who specializes in nude figure painting, Mami is his favorite subject, and watercolor nudes of her are frequently shown during the show, as well as Mami's modeling.

As a result of this, her lack of any qualms about being nude around the house is a running theme in the show -- many episodes had Mami nude for extended periods of time while she posed for her father, usually interrupting his painting when she thought of some solution to a problem (or her powers warned her of a developing problem).

title: rafute
body:
"Rafute is a pork rib dish in the Okinawan cuisine of the island of Okinawa, Japan. Rafute is skin-on pork rib stewed in soy sauce and brown sugar. It is traditionally considered to help with longevity. Rafute was originally a form of Okinawan Royal Cuisine.

"In Hawaii, rafute is known as "shoyu pork," which is served in plate lunches. In the early 1900s, Okinawan immigrants in Hawaii introduced rafute into the local cuisine. They likely did so through food services, as ethnic Okinawans owned and ran many restaurants in Honolulu, Hawaii." [1]

title: teresa_linares
body: [[Tales of Berseria]] character. [[Oscar Dragonia]]'s older half-sister. She protects her younger brother with fervor because he was the only one who treated her well. She harbors great resentment against [[velvet crowe|Velvet]] for wounding Oscar's eye. Her seiyuu is [[Horie Yui]].

title: seres_(tales)
body: [[Tales of Berseria]] character. A masked, red-haired malak who helped [[velvet crowe|Velvet]] escape from Titania Prison, but after she suffered a fatal blow, she asked Velvet to devour her. This resulted in the Sorcerer's Ring being made.

title: oscar_dragonia

title: artorius_collbrande

title: spada_belforma
body: An aristocratic young man who left his family [spoiler]due to familial abuse[/spoiler] and has been traveling since. title: ruca_milda
body: The main hero of [[Tales of Innocence]]. Ruca is timid and antisocial, but helps [[Iria Animi]] escape from pursuers because those with "powers" are arrested. Ruca also gains such abilities, starting their journey. [spoiler]He used to be Asura in his past life, but his personality was split into two upon his death - Ruca is the "good" half of Asura.[/spoiler]

title: orifiel_(tales)
body: A strategist and magician who used to be [[asura (tales)|Asura]]'s enemy. [spoiler]In an odd twist, he is reincarnated as Ange Serena, and she transforms into Orifiel when performing her Mystic Arte.[/spoiler] Something to think about there...

title: mathias_(tales)
body: The main antagonist of [[Tales of Innocence]] who seeks destruction of heaven and earth so everyone will be "equal". [spoiler]Like Ruca, Mathias was also Asura in her past life, but his personality split upon his death - Mathias is the "evil" half of Asura, filled with bitter rage and hatred after Inanna and Durandal killed him. To mock Inanna, he took upon her face as Mathias.[/spoiler]

title: iria_animi
body: The main heroine of [[Tales of Innocence]], Iria is an impulsive gunslinger who is being chased at the beginning of the game. She is rescued by Ruca, but this starts their journey into what their and others' special "powers" are. [spoiler]Iria used to be Inanna in her past life, who betrayed the god Asura by stabbing him in the back with Durandal.[/spoiler]

title: inanna_(tales)
body: [[asura (tales)|Asura]]'s lover, [spoiler]but was actually sent to assassinate him. She is reborn as Iria Animi.[/spoiler]

title: hypnos
body: The Grim Reaper and former enemy of [[asura (tales)|Asura]], but he slew Hypnos during the game's first battle. [spoiler]He is reincarnated as Ricardo Soldato.[/spoiler]

title: himmel_(tales)
body: Minor [[Tales of Innocence]] character. Orifiel's student who was captured by Ratio. [spoiler]He is killed, then reincarnated as Albert Grandeioza.[/spoiler]

title: hermana_larmo
body: An orphaned girl who lives on the street, fending for herself with powerful martial arts moves. [spoiler]She used to be the ancient dragon Vrtra in her past life.[/spoiler]

title: hasta_ekstermi
body: [[Tales of Innocence]] antagonist. A deranged man who seeks to destroy everything, and loves to kill everyone he sees. [spoiler]He is the reincarnation of the demon spear Gae Bolg.[/spoiler]
other_names: ハスタ・エクステルミ

title: durandal_(tales)
body: [[Asras]]' holy sword, who was sentient. Durandal had been given to him as a gift [spoiler]but was really sent for Inanna to kill him. Durandal is reincarnated as Spada Belforma.[/spoiler]

title: qq_selesneva
body: [[Tales of Innocence R]] character. A woman from another world claiming to be an archaeologist who is curious about Ruca's world.
other_names: キュキュ・セレツネワ

title: coda_(tales)
body: Minor [[Tales of Innocence]] character. A small creature that always accompanies [[Iria Animi]].

title: chitose_charma
body: [[Tales of Innocence]] antagonist. A member of the organization Arca, who approaches [[Ruca Milda]] but has tensions against [[Iria Animi]]. [spoiler]She is the reincarnation of the flower goddess Sakuya.[/spoiler]

title: ange_serena
body: A skillful young woman who has healing powers and is dexterous enough to steal. [spoiler]She used to be the (male) tactician Orifiel in her past life.[/spoiler] Her seiyuu is [[Nazuka Kaori]].

title: asura_(tales)
body: A god who wanted to reunite heaven and earth to bring peace, and was [[inanna (tales)|Inanna]]'s lover. His sword was [[durandal (tales)|Durandal]]. [spoiler]His "good" half is reincarnated as Ruca Milda, while his "evil", hate-filled half manifests as Mathias after Inanna and Durandal betrayed and killed him.[/spoiler] His seiyuu is [[Koyama Rikiya]].

title: legretta_(tales)
body: One of the Six God Generals in [[Tales of the Abyss]], mainly the antagonist to [[Tear Grants]]. Legretta used to be Tear's mentor, and she cares for her well-being by imploring her to leave the party. Legretta fights with dual-wielding magic guns and uses light-based magic.

title: gelda_nebilim
body: Minor [[Tales of the Abyss]] character. [[Jade Curtiss]]' former teacher, who sought to change the boy's twisted heart so he could put his research towards the greater good.

title: florian_(tales)

title: dist_(tales)
body: One of the Six God Generals in [[Tales of the Abyss]], though he doesn't share their goals. Dist is only interested in furthering his research and proving himself to his childhood rival [[Jade Curtiss]], but Jade coldly ignores him. Dist is the only one the party never directly fights - they instead fight his mechanical creations. His seiyuu is [[Yao Kazuki]].

title: stella_telmes
body:
[[Shirley Fennes]]' older sister in [[Tales of Legendia]] who went missing 3 years ago and believed to be dead. [[Senel Coolidge]] is in love with her and is burdened with her disappearance. Her seiyuu is [[Sonozaki Mie]].

[spoiler]She had been alive this whole time as the Legacy's will. Stella dies protecting the surface from a shot fired from the Legacy.[/spoiler]

title: shirley_fennes
body: The main heroine of [[Tales of Legendia]], Shirley is a girl prophesied to be the Merines, a communicator with the will of the sea Nerifes. She is caring towards others, but suffers an inferiority complex and feels isolated from being constantly endangered. Her seiyuu is [[Hirohashi Ryou]].
other_names: シャーリィ・フェンネス

title: senel_coolidge
body: The main hero of [[Tales of Legendia]] and the first hero to not use a sword in battle; he uses his fists instead. Senel acts like a brother to [[Shirley Fennes]] and helps her escape from those who want her powers. Senel doesn't trust others very quickly and tends to make irrational decisions, but learns from them quickly. His seiyuu is [[Suzumura Ken'ichi]].

title: norma_beatty
body: A protagonist in [[Tales of Legendia]] who works as a treasure hunter by herself before meeting [[Senel Coolidge]]'s party. Norma has a habit of nicknaming everyone she meets, although she doesn't give herself one ([[moses sandor|Moses]] does call her 'Bubbles' though). Her seiyuu is [[Mizuhashi Kaori]].

title: shigure_rangetsu
body: [[Tales of Berseria]] character. [[rokurou rangetsu|Rokurou]]'s older brother. Shigure is a high-ranking legate for the Abbey, but he's only interested in finding strong opponents. Rokurou is driven to defeat Shigure in battle. His seiyuu is [[Nakai Kazuya]], who also voices [[Moses Sandor]] in [[Tales of Legendia]].

title: jay_(tales)
body: A protagonist in [[Tales of Legendia]] who gathers intelligence and provides information before crucial battles. Jay used to be a child assassin, but was found by the Oresoren tribe and raised into who he is today. Jay is annoying and cynical, especially towards [[Moses Sandor]], but is hard on himself. His seiyuu is [[Shiraishi Ryouko]].

title: grune_(tales)
body: An unknown and bizarre woman in [[Tales of Legendia]] who doesn't remember anything but her name. This doesn't bother her a lot, since Grune is unbelievably dense and prone to getting lost. She just goes along with the flow and joins the party for no particular reason. Her seiyuu is [[Kawasumi Ayako]].

title: karada
body: A rope dress typically takes around 10-15 m of rope to tie, and involves multiple passes of rope from front to back around the body to build up the characteristic diamond-shaped rope pattern, typically starting from a rope halter and moving down the body. In some cases, a rope harness may extend beyond the torso, into diamond-patterned webs that extend down the length of the arms or legs.

title: veigue_lungberg
body: The main hero of [[Tales of Rebirth]], Veigue is a quiet young man who is attached to his childhood friend [[Claire Bennett]]. His scream, "CLAIIIIIIRE!" has become a meme even in the Tales series. His seiyuu is [[Hiyama Nobuyuki]].
other_names: ヴェイグ・リュングベル

title: tytree_crowe
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] character. A hot-headed boy from Petnadjanka who joins the group to rescue his kidnapped sister. His seiyuu is [[Yamaguchi Kappei]].

title: saleh
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] antagonist. One of the Four Stars, a sadistic human who takes pleasure in others' suffering.

title: mao_(tales)
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] character. A boy with amnesia who travels with [[Eugene Gallardo]]. He uses the Force of Fire in battle.

title: hilda_rhambling
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] character. A Half born between a human father and a Gajuma mother, who has a dark past of being bullied by both races alike. Her seiyuu is [[Oohara Sayaka]].
other_names: ヒルダ・ランブリング

title: eugene_gallardo
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] character. The former Commander of Calegia's forces who was exiled for killing [[Annie Barrs]]' father. He is a black panther Gajuma, a type of beastman in the game. His seiyuu is [[Ishizuka Unshou]].
other_names: ユージーン・ガラルド

title: annie_barrs
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] character. She seeks revenge against [[Eugene Gallardo]] for the death of her father, and developed a hatred of Gajuma as a result. Her seiyuu is [[Yajima Akiko]].

title: agarte_lindblum
body: [[Tales of Rebirth]] character. She ordered for the most beautiful girl in the kingdom to be brought to her, sparking the protagonists' adventure. Her seiyuu is [[Shinohara Emi]].
other_names: アガーテ・リンドブロム

title: richter_abend
body: A character in [[Tales of Symphonia Knight of Ratatosk]] who appears cold and cynical, but doesn't hold anything against others. He especially despises cowards. He gives [[Emil Castagnier]] this piece of inspirational advice: "Courage is the magic that turns dreams into reality." His seiyuu is [[Hamada Kenji]].
other_names: リヒター・アーベント

title: marta_lualdi
body: The female protagonist of [[Tales of Symphonia Knight of Ratatosk]]. Marta is madly in love with co-star [[Emil Castagnier]] because she believes he saved her during a massacre that occurred six months prior to the game. Her seiyuu is [[Kugimiya Rie]].

title: nanaly_fletch
body: A protagonist in [[Tales of Destiny 2]] who serves as the team's archer. Nanaly is self-assured and seems like a tomboy, but is a caring young woman who helps raise orphans in her home of Hope Town. Her seiyuu [[Kawakami Tomoko]] passed away in 2011 and has been replaced by Kakazu Yumi.

title: loni_dunamis
body: A protagonist in [[Tales of Destiny 2]] who was raised in the same orphanage as [[Kyle Dunamis]]. Loni acts like Kyle's big brother, but has a tendency to try and woo women. He also helps [[Nanaly Fletch]] comes to terms with her past. His seiyuu is [[Seki Toshihiko]].

title: harold_berselius
body: A protagonist in [[Tales of Destiny 2]]. Despite the name, Harold is female - she deliberately chose the name to fool historians. She is the classic eccentric genius who always thinks about her research, and is otherwise inept with real life affairs. Harold is childish and unpredictable, but also very perceptive.
other_names: ハロルド・ベルセリオス

title: elraine_(tales)
body: The main antagonist of [[Tales of Destiny 2]] who serves in the Order of Atamoni as a miracle worker, believing she is an extension of the goddess Fortuna. She seeks to make everyone "happy" by forcefully rewriting the history of the A'ether Wars.

title: dymlos_timber
body: [[Tales of Destiny 2]] character. The personality of the Swordian of Fire, Dymlos. He was the Division Commander of the 1st Er'ther Army unit during the Aeth'er Wars.
other_names: ディムロス・ティンバー

title: atwight_eks
body: [[Tales of Destiny 2]] character. The personality of the Swordian of Water, Atwight. She served as Medical Corps Colonel during the Aeth'er Wars.
other_names: アトワイト・エックス

title: fog_(tales)
body: [[Tales of Eternia]] character. Renamed [b]Max[/b] in the English version.

title: stahn_aileron
body: The main hero of [[Tales of Destiny]], older brother of [[Lilith Aileron]], and father of [[Kyle Dunamis]]. Stahn is a country bumpkin who happens upon the Swordian of Fire, Dymlos, during his quest to become famous. This chance encounter drags them into the middle of a plot involving the dreaded Eye of Atamoni. While good-natured, Stahn can come off as an idiot. His seiyuu is [[Seki Tomokazu]].

title: philia_felice
body: A charming but fastidious priestess in [[Tales of Destiny]] who resides at Straylize Temple to do research on the A'ether Wars. She was turned into stone by a fellow priest, but cured by [[Stahn Aileron]]'s party. During the journey, Philia obtains the Swordian of Lightning, Clemente. Ironically, she does not use any healing magic at all despite being a priestess. Her seiyuu is [[Inoue Kikuko]].

title: leon_magnus
body:
A protagonist in [[Tales of Destiny]]. Leon is very brooding and complex at times, and is the youngest swordmaster to serve the kingdom at age 16. He only opens up to a maid named Marian. Leon wields the Swordian of Earth, Chaltier. His seiyuu is [[Midorikawa Hikaru]].

[spoiler]He is Rutee Katrea's younger brother, his real name being Emilio Katrea. Sadly, Leon does not survive to help Stahn and Rutee fight the final battle due to his injuries and tremendous guilt.[/spoiler]

title: woodrow_kelvin
body: [[Tales of Destiny]] character. The prince of Phandaria, and wielder of the Swordian Igtenos. Renamed [b]Garr Kelvin[/b] in the English version.
other_names: ウッドロウ・ケルヴィン

title: mary_argent
body: A protagonist in [[Tales of Destiny]] who is [[Rutee Katrea]]'s partner in seeking riches. She has no Swordian, but is a formidable opponent regardless.
other_names: マリー・エージェント

title: lilith_aileron
body: The younger sister of [[Tales of Destiny]]'s main hero [[Stahn Aileron]]. She worries about her brother and wishes he wouldn't go on such dangerous adventures. Lilith is not playable in the original PS1 version, but becomes playable in the PS2 remake.

title: goliath_tracked_mine
body:
Officially designed as the Leichter Ladungsträger Goliath (Sd.Kfz. 302/303a/303b), the Goliath tracked mine was also called the Beetle Tank by allies soldiers because it looks like a small tank. 

Packed with explosives, these were remotely controlled. Unfortunately, a long cable was required between it and the user and this could be easily severed or damaged. The mine itself had weak armor and a low speed and most were destroyed or captured. Although it proved useless for Germany in [[World War II]], it proved to be the basis of unmanned vehicles.

title: lifting_body
body:
A lifting body is a fixed-wing aircraft or spacecraft configuration in which the body itself produces lift. In contrast to a flying wing, which is a wing with minimal or no conventional fuselage, a lifting body can be thought of as a fuselage with little or no conventional wing. Whereas a flying wing seeks to maximize cruise efficiency at subsonic speeds by eliminating non-lifting surfaces, lifting bodies generally minimize the drag and structure of a wing for subsonic, supersonic, and hypersonic flight, or, spacecraft re-entry.

Not to be confused with [[lifting]] or [[carrying]] tags.

h4. See also

* [[airplane]]
* [[carrying]]

title: byakko
body:
[b]Bai Hu[/b] (白虎) is the White Tiger, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. In Chinese culture, the tiger is the king of the beasts and has been presented with a 王 on his forehead for centuries. According to legend, the tiger's tail would turn white when it reached the age of 500 years. In this way, the white tiger became a kind of mythological creature. It was said that the white tiger would only appear when the emperor ruled with absolute virtue, or if there was peace throughout the world. It is known as Bai Hu in Chinese, Baek-ho in Korean, Byakko in Japanese and Bạch Hổ in Vietnamese. It represents the west and the autumn season.

h4. See also

* [[Seiryuu]], azure dragon of the east
* [[Genbu]], black tortoise of the north
* [[Suzaku]], vermilion bird of the south

title: genbu
body:
[b]Xuan Wu[/b] (玄龜) is the Black Tortoise/Black Turtle, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. Despite its English name, it is usually depicted as a turtle entwined together with a snake. Further, in East Asia, it is not called after either animal but is instead known as the "Black Warrior" under various local pronunciations. It is known as Xuan Wu (or sometimes Xuan Gui) in Chinese, Hyeon-mu in Korean, Genbu in Japanese and Huyền Vũ in Vietnamese. It represents the north and the winter season.

h4. See also

* [[Seiryuu]], azure dragon of the east
* [[Byakko]], white tiger of the west
* [[Suzaku]], vermilion bird of the south

title: seiryuu
body:
[b]Qing Long[/b] (青龍) is the Azure Dragon, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. It should not be confused with the mythological yellow dragon that is associated with the Emperor of China. It is also referred to in media, feng shui, other cultures, and in various venues as the Green Dragon and the Avalon Dragon. It is known as Qing Long in Chinese, Cheong-ryong in Korean, Seiryuu in Japanese and Thanh Long in Vietnamese. It represents the east and the spring season.

h4. See also

* [[Byakko]], white tiger of the west
* [[Genbu]], black tortoise of the north

title: suzaku
body:
[b]Zhu Que[/b] (朱雀) is the Vermilion Bird, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. It is described as a red bird that resembles a pheasant with a five-colored plumage and is perpetually covered in flames. It is often mistaken for the Fenghuang due to similarities in appearance, but the two are different creatures. It is known as Zhu Que (or sometimes Zhu Qiao) in Chinese, Ju-jak in Korean, Suzaku/Shujaku in Japanese and Chu Tước in Vietnamese. It represents the south and the summer season.

title: wilhelm_burgdorf
body:
Wilhelm Burgdorf (15 February 1895 – 2 May 1945) was one of 4 generals in the OKH's Chief of Staff, and held the post of Chief of the Army Personnel Office (Heerespersonalamt) and Chief Adjutant to Adolf Hitler. Historians have noted that Burgdorf in the latter stages of the war consumed alcohol heavily and got angry very easily.

After failed surrender negotiations he attempted to shoot Hans Fritzsche after the latter intended to surrender to Soviet Marshall Georgy Zhukov. On May 2nd 1945 he and his colleague Hans Krebs commited suicide in the Führerbunker.

He is portrayed by Justus von Dohnányi in the 2004 movie Der Untergang.

He appears in the second cour of the series, still bitter over the events of the manga and joining [[altair (re:creators)|Altair]]'s faction purely to take him down.

title: hans_krebs
body:
Hans Krebs (March 4th 1898 - May 2nd 1945) was a Wehrmacht general and one of 4 generals in the OKH's Chief of Staff (the others being Keitel, Jodl and Burgdorf.)

He was the one who opened surrender negotiations after the suicide of Hitler, but due to the refusal of Goebbels to adhere to terms of unconditional surrender they ended with no agreement and soon after; on May 2nd 1945, Krebs and Burgdorf commited suicide in the Führerbunker.

He is portrayed by Rolf Kanies in the 2004 movie, Der Untergang.
